datatable(rel_by_region)
rel_by_region <- gss_sm |> 
  group_by(bigregion, religion) |> 
  summarise(N = n()) |> 
  mutate(prop = N/sum(N),
         pct = round(100 * prop, 2))

datatable(rel_by_region)

option + command + I for mac alt + ctrl + I for windwos

ggplot(rel_by_region,
       aes(x = pct, y = religion, fill = religion)) +
  geom_col() +
  facet_wrap(.~bigregion, nrow = 1) +
  guides(fill = "none")

organdata <- organdata

organdata |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = donors,
             y = country)) +
  geom_boxplot()

organdata |> 
  mutate(country = fct_reorder(country,
                               donors, na.rm = T)) |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = donors,
             y = country)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  labs(y = NULL)

p <- ggplot(data = organdata,
            mapping = 
              aes(x = 
                    reorder(
                      country, 
                      donors, 
                      na.rm=TRUE),
                  y = donors, 
                  fill = world))
p + geom_boxplot() + 
  labs(x=NULL) +
  coord_flip() + 
  theme(legend.position = "top")

by_country <- organdata |> group_by(consent_law, country) |>
    summarize(donors_mean= mean(donors, na.rm = TRUE),
              donors_sd = sd(donors, na.rm = TRUE),
              gdp_mean = mean(gdp, na.rm = TRUE),
              health_mean = mean(health, na.rm = TRUE),
              roads_mean = mean(roads, na.rm = TRUE),
              cerebvas_mean = mean(cerebvas, na.rm = TRUE))
by_country <- organdata |> group_by(consent_law, country) |>
  summarise_if(is.numeric,
               lst(mean, sd), na.rm = T)

p <- ggplot(elections_historic, aes(x = popular_pct, y = ec_pct,
                                    label = winner_label))
p_title <- "Presidential Elections: Popular & Electoral College Margins"
p_subtitle <- "1824-2016"
p_caption <- "Data for 2016 are provisional."
x_label <- "Winner's share of Popular Vote"
y_label <- "Winner's share of Electoral College Votes"

p <- p + 
    geom_hline(yintercept = 0.5, 
               linewidth = 1.4, 
               color = "gray80") +
    geom_vline(xintercept = 0.5, 
               linewidth = 1.4, 
               color = "gray80") +
    geom_point() +
    geom_text_repel() + 
     scale_x_continuous(
       labels = scales::percent) +
     scale_y_continuous(
       labels = scales::percent)  + 
  labs(x = x_label, 
         y = y_label, 
         title = p_title, 
         subtitle = p_subtitle,
         caption = p_caption)
p

p <- ggplot(data = by_country,
            mapping = 
              aes(x = gdp_mean,
                  y = health_mean))
p + geom_point() +
    geom_text_repel(
      data = filter(by_country, 
                    gdp_mean > 25000),
      mapping = 
        aes(label = country))

p <- ggplot(data = by_country,
            mapping = 
              aes(x = gdp_mean, 
                  y = health_mean))
p + geom_point() +
    geom_text_repel(
      data = 
        filter(by_country,
               gdp_mean > 25000 | 
                 health_mean < 1500 |
                 country %in% "Belgium"),
      mapping = 
        aes(label = country))

# creating a dummy variable for labels
# organdata$ind <- 
#   organdata$ccode %in% c("Ita", "Spa") & 
#   organdata$year > 1998   

organdata <- organdata |> 
  mutate(ind = ccode %in% c("Ita", "Spa") & year > 1998)

p <- ggplot(data = organdata,
            mapping = 
              aes(x = roads, 
                  y = donors, 
                  color = ind))
p + geom_point() +
    geom_text_repel(
      data = filter(organdata, ind),
      mapping = aes(label = ccode)) +
    guides(label = "none", 
           color = "none")

mtcars <- datasets::mtcars
mtcars$model <- rownames(mtcars)
rownames(mtcars) <- 1:nrow(mtcars)

mtcars |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = wt, y = mpg)) +
  geom_point(color = "red") +
  geom_text_repel(
    data = filter(mtcars,
                  wt > 5),
    aes(label = model)
  )

p <- ggplot(data = organdata, 
            mapping = 
              aes(x = roads, 
                  y = donors))

  annotate(geom = "text", 
           x = 91, y = 33,
           label = "A surprisingly high \n recovery rate.",
           hjust = 0)

            mapping = aes(x = roads, y = donors))

             fill = "red", 
             alpha = 0.2) +

             x = 157, y = 33,
             label = "A surprisingly high \n recovery rate.", 
             hjust = 0)

```{r setup}
library(ggrepel)

theme_set(theme_ipsum()+
          theme(strip.background =element_rect(fill="lightgray"),
                axis.title.x = 
                  element_text(angle = 0,
                               size = rel(1.33),
                               margin = margin(10,0,0,0)),
                axis.title.y = 
                  element_text(angle = 90,
                               size = rel(1.33),
```

```{r}
#| fig-width: 12
#| fig-height: 12

p_title <- "Presidential Elections: Popular & Electoral College Margins"
p_subtitle <- "1824-2016"
p_caption <- "Data for 2016 are provisional."
x_label <- "Winner's share of Popular Vote"
y_label <- "Winner's share of Electoral College Votes"

p <- p + 
    geom_hline(yintercept = 0.5, 
               linewidth = 1.4, 
               color = "gray80") +
    geom_vline(xintercept = 0.5, 
               linewidth = 1.4, 
               color = "gray80") +
    geom_point() +
    geom_text_repel() + 
     scale_x_continuous(
       labels = scales::percent) +
     scale_y_continuous(
       labels = scales::percent)  + 
  labs(x = x_label, 
         y = y_label, 
         title = p_title, 
         subtitle = p_subtitle,
         caption = p_caption)
p
```

```{r}
            mapping = 
              aes(x = gdp_mean, 
                  y = health_mean))
```

```{r}
    geom_text_repel(
      data = 
        filter(by_country,
               gdp_mean > 25000 | 
                 health_mean < 1500 |
                 country %in% "Belgium"),
```

```{r}
# creating a dummy variable for labels
# organdata$ind <- 
#   organdata$ccode %in% c("Ita", "Spa") & 
#   organdata$year > 1998   

organdata <- organdata |> 
  mutate(ind = ccode %in% c("Ita", "Spa") & year > 1998)

p <- ggplot(data = organdata,
            mapping = 
              aes(x = roads, 
                  y = donors, 
                  color = ind))
p + geom_point() +
    geom_text_repel(
      data = filter(organdata, ind),
      mapping = aes(label = ccode)) +
    guides(label = "none", 
           color = "none")
```

```{r}
mtcars <- datasets::mtcars
```
